source:  HarfBuzz 14.2.1, vendored as a shaping subset (the amalgamation and
         its headers; no tests, no optional integrations).
tag:     14.2.1
url:     https://github.com/harfbuzz/harfbuzz
license: "Old MIT" (LICENSE beside this file = upstream COPYING).

Consumed by LÖVE's love.font (src/modules/font/freetype/HarfbuzzShaper.cpp)
per readme.md's build map ("vendored from outside: HarfBuzz — LÖVE 12 requires
it for text shaping").

SUBSET — what is vendored and why:
  src/**/*.{cc,hh,h}   the whole shaping source, INCLUDING the OT/ (OpenType),
                       ms-use/ (Universal Shaping Engine), and graph/ trees the
                       amalgamation pulls in. Built as ONE translation unit via
                       the upstream unified source src/harfbuzz.cc (which
                       #includes hb-ft.cc and hb-static.cc).
  Dropped: test-*/main*/*-test/fuzzer sources, the rust/ and wasm/ optional
  integrations, and non-source artifacts (.py, .rl, .in, shaders) — none
  reached by the amalgamation in this configuration.

BUILD CONFIG (in build.sh, no generated config.h needed — HarfBuzz uses its
hb-config.hh defaults plus these -D flags):
  -DHAVE_FREETYPE=1   enable the hb-ft FreeType integration LÖVE uses; needs
                      wasi/vendor/freetype/include on the include path (a
                      vendor-to-vendor dependency, resolved by build.sh).
  -DHB_NO_MT          single-threaded (wasm has no threads here); drops atomics.
  -std=c++17          HarfBuzz's minimum.
  Other backends (coretext, directwrite, glib, icu, cairo, graphite2, gobject)
  stay off — their HAVE_* macros are undefined, so those .cc bodies compile empty.

Built to a static archive by build.sh; witnessed by run.sh (shapes "Hello"
with hb-ft over Vera.ttf and checks the glyph run) under node + Chromium +
Firefox. Update by re-dropping the subset from a newer release and refreshing
this PIN. Never edit upstream files in place.
